Flask News Application

This Flask application provides a simple interface to view top headlines and search for news articles based on various criteria like topic, date range, and language. It utilizes the News API to fetch current news from around the world.

Features
View top headlines from a selected country.
Search for news articles by topic, date range, sort by criteria, and language.
Pagination support for search results.

Getting Started

Prerequisites
Python 3.6 or higher
pip and virtualenv

Installation
Clone the repository
sh
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/dita-nova/news_api
cd yourrepositoryname
Create and activate a virtual environment

On Windows:
cmd
Copy code
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate

On Unix or MacOS:
sh
Copy code
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Install the required packages
sh
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt

Configuration
Obtain a free API key from News API.
Create a .env file in the root directory and add your API key:
env
Copy code
NEWS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
Ensure to replace your_api_key_here with your actual News API key.

Running the Application
With the configuration set, you can start the server using:

sh
Copy code
flask run
Access the web application at http://localhost:5000 in your browser.

Usage

Top Headlines: Navigate to /top-headlines to view the top headlines from a selected country.
Search News: Use the form on the home page to search for news articles by specifying a topic, date range, and other criteria.

